3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel algorithm for action anticipation, which is a subfield of AI. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses a Recurrent Neural Network-based algorithm for feature generation and action anticipation. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics): The proposed algorithm can be applied in robotics for anticipating human actions and improving human-robot interaction.
